# BrightHive Engineering-Leader Onboarding
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in YOUR OWN credentials.
# This file is read by the Makefile targets in Layer 1 (onboarding primitives).
#
# What goes here: things ONLY YOU have. AWS profile names, your LastPass user,
# your GitHub token.
#
# What does NOT go here: shared BrightHive secrets — those live in the vaults
# (aws-secrets-vault, dynamo-vault, lastpass-vault) and are pulled into
# ./secrets/ by `make pull-secrets`.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS SSO profile names (after you've run `aws configure sso` for each)
# Default profile names match what /aws-auth skill expects.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AWS_MAIN_PROFILE=brighthive-main
AWS_STAGING_PROFILE=brighthive-staging
AWS_PRODUCTION_PROFILE=brighthive-production

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# YOUR LastPass account (you'll be prompted for password by `lpass login`)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
LASTPASS_USER=you@brighthive.io

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# YOUR GitHub personal access token
# Required scopes: repo, read:org
# Generate at: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_REPLACE_ME

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: where sibling repos live (default: parent dir of this repo)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SIBLINGS_DIR=../

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: secrets cache TTL in seconds (default: 86400 = 24h)
# Use FORCE=1 on any pull-* target to ignore the cache for one run.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SECRETS_CACHE_TTL=86400
